node.accessibility_caption: Photo by Lex Fridman on July 25, 2021. May be an image of 2 people, people sitting and indoor.

node.text:
Reposted from @hubermanlab - I had a great time talking to my friend Andrew on his podcast. This looks like I'm making him an offer he can't refuse.
-
My recent conversation with @lexfridman surprised me and forever changed the way I think about relationships of all kinds. What was especially striking to me was how a conversation about machines, robots and artificial intelligence could reveal so much about what we fundamentally need from others and from ourselves. Thank you for the many insights Lex and for articulating them so clearly for all of us to learn and benefit.
-
You can find our conversation (in video and/or audio format) at the link in my profile bio or by searching Huberman Lab @youtube @applepodcasts or @spotifypodcasts 
-
New episodes of the Huberman Lab Podcast out every Monday. Please leave any comments or suggestions for future episode content in the comments section below this post, or on my YouTube channel. Also, if you’re not already listening to the Lex Fridman Podcast, I can’t recommend it highly enough! Thank you for your interest in science!
-
Photo credit: @blabacphoto 
-
@hubermanlab @stanford.med @stanford @nihgov @nimhgov @nih_nccih @societyforneuroscience @mitscience 
-

node.text: This is the view from a hike I took while visiting @anyafernald at @belcampomeatco in northern California. New podcast conversation with Anya is now up on YouTube. It felt incredible to escape out into nature for a few days with good people, good food, and good conversation.

node.accessibility_caption: Photo by Lex Fridman on July 20, 2021. May be an image of dog and outdoors.

node.text: This is Homer, as in Homer Simpson. He was my long-time friend until he passed away over a decade ago. As I mentioned to @hubermanlab, who lost his dog Costello recently, I miss Homer to this day. Now I'm thinking about getting a 4-legged friend again (aside from the robots).

node.accessibility_caption: Photo by Lex Fridman on July 19, 2021. May be a black-and-white image of 2 people and beard.

node.text: I really enjoyed talking to the brilliant @hubermanlab on his podcast. He is an incredible scientist, educator, and human being, and I'm honored to be able to call him a friend. Our conversation is now up on his YouTube and everywhere else.

node.accessibility_caption: Photo by Lex Fridman on July 15, 2021. May be an image of 2 people, people standing and military uniform.

node.text: My conversation with @michaelmalice for the 200th episode of the podcast is up on YouTube. We laughed, we cried, we had fun. This has been an amazing journey for me. I'm grateful for all the support & love along the way. From the bottom of my heart: thank you.

node.accessibility_caption: Photo by Lex Fridman on July 11, 2021. May be an image of 1 person and beard.

node.text: This is Roger Reaves, one of the most prolific drug smugglers in history, working for Pablo Escobar and the Medellin Cartel. He was the employer & close friend of the infamous Barry Seal. I just released a podcast episode with him on YouTube and elsewhere. This was unlike any conversation I've ever had.

node.accessibility_caption: Photo by Lex Fridman on July 10, 2021. May be an image of 1 person.

node.text:
Congrats to Argentina for winning Copa America today, Lionel Messi's first. I've been a huge fan of Messi since 2004 and his early days at Barcelona & Argentina. At that time, and for years since, he played the most beautiful football I have ever seen, and may ever see.

#messi

node.accessibility_caption: Photo by Lex Fridman on July 08, 2021. May be an image of sky and skyscraper.

node.text:
Late night run along the river in Austin.

I've been going through a bit of a rough time, but I can always count on a run, especially at night, to make me feel better and remind me that life is full of beautiful moments that are easy to see if we just pause and look.
